Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "podići" in different forms and positions:

1. *Podigao* sam ruke u znak predaje. (I raised my hands in a sign of surrender.)
2. Oni *podižu* novu zgradu u gradu. (They are building a new building in the city.)
3. Želim da *podignem* kredit za kupovinu kuće. (I want to take out a loan to buy a house.)
4. Kada *podigneš* kutiju, pripazi da ne povrediš leđa. (When you lift the box, be careful not to hurt your back.)
5. Koliko si puta danas već *podigao* telefon? (How many times have you already picked up the phone today?)
6. Oni su *podišli* na vrh brda kako bi videli zalazak sunca. (They climbed to the top of the hill to watch the sunset.)
7. *Podići* ćemo ogradu oko vrta da bismo zaštitili biljke. (We will put up a fence around the garden to protect the plants.)
8. Kada si *podigao* novac sa bankomata? (When did you withdraw money from the ATM?)
9. Ona je uspela da *podigne* svoj biznis sa nule. (She managed to build her business from scratch.)
10. Molim vas da *podignete* glas, ne čujem vas dobro. (Please speak up, I can't hear you well.)

I hope these examples help!